data.comment:
I decided to come back to doing Celeste speedruns again very recently. One of the things I wanted to improve was any Any% time. I had done runs casually over a long span without ever submitting or uploading the runs. I have had a good streak of PB's recently so I think its time I submit a run to the leaderboard.



Overall this was a very good run. I keep managing to pull off time improvements without any major adjustments to my route, but I expect that will be changing sometime soon. None of the stages went poorly for my standards, and I had a few really substantial golds in Golden Ridge and Mirror Temple specifically. I got over a minute and a half of time save in the stretch from Resort to Temple which went a long way in getting both sub 48 and sub 47 in the same run.



I want to go for sub 45 soon but I will probably need to learn stats for specific rooms and optimize my route further before I can get it. The downside of this run is that it is just 22 seconds slower than my current sum of best...
